Citation.sTitle: Determination and correlation of liquid-liquid equilibria for nine binary acetonitrile + n-alkane systems
Citation.sAbstract: Liquid-liquid equilibrium (LLE) measurements for nine binary acetonitrile + n-alkane (octane,  nonane, decane, undecane, dodecane, tridecane, tetradecane, pentadecane, and hexadecane) systems  were performed using a laser light scattering technique at moderate pressure from 350 K to the  upper critical solution temperature. Experimentally determined cloud points for biphasic acetonitrile  systems are essential for efficient design and extraction process development for the recently  proposed and effective oxidative desulfurization method. These LLE data were satisfactorily  correlated with the NRTL equation.
